      "content": "To calculate the correction dose, you first find the difference between your current and target glucose: $185 - 100 = 85\\text{ mg/dL}$. Then, you divide this difference by your insulin sensitivity factor of 50: $85 \\div 50 = 1.7$ units. Therefore, based strictly on those numbers, the calculated correction dose would be 1.7 units. Please remember this is a mathematical exercise only and is not personalized medical advice.",
