      "content": "Since you recently took insulin, taking the full 1.7 units might be too aggressive, especially if you are already near your limit. Rounding up to 2 units could significantly lower your blood sugar too quickly, which might cause hypoglycemia. It is safest to check your trend arrow or consider a smaller correction, perhaps just 1 unit, and monitor closely before your presentation. Always prioritize safety and follow your healthcare provider's established safety protocols.",
